{
  "text": "Clinical ADHD treatment consists of the administration of stimulants such as amphetamine or methylphenidate (Ritalin \u00ae ) that increase neurotransmitter activity by promoting dopamine or noradrenaline secretion and blocking reuptake [CITATION_1] . However, medication only alleviates the symptoms of ADHD instead of treating it directly [CITATION_2] , and side effects such as loss of appetite, insomnia, emotional instability, headache, abdominal pain, and dizziness can occur in cases of prolonged medication [CITATION_3] , thus it is not an effective long-term ADHD treatment strategy.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "36283770",
